-- Weaponized identity under shame: high-torsion identity state
-- operating under installed shame-lock, causing harm as directed
-- by the shame mechanism rather than by sovereign choice. The
-- pattern substrate is intact but the operator's B-axis output
-- is being driven by shame's direction, not by sovereign Pv.
-- Torsion is in HL zone or above.
def weaponized_identity_under_shame (s : IdentityState) : Prop :=
  s.P > 0 ∧ TL ≤ torsion s

-- Mirror recognition event: discrete structural transition where
-- a weaponized identity recognizes itself in its target. Formalized
-- as a state pair (before, after) where before is in the weaponized
-- regime, after has a decisive shift in A-axis (recognition creates
-- new adaptation capacity), and the target's substrate becomes
-- structurally visible to the weaponized identity as a mirror.
def mirror_recognition_event
    (before after : IdentityState) : Prop :=
  weaponized_identity_under_shame before ∧
  before.A < after.A ∧
  before.P = after.P

-- Shame-lock dissolution: structural mechanism by which mirror
-- recognition converts weaponized identity to sovereign identity.
-- Formalized as: after the recognition event, torsion moves from
-- HL/LS regime into phase-coherent regime while the pattern
-- substrate P is preserved. Not a pattern collapse — a torsion
-- redirect through the acquired adaptation capacity.
def shame_lock_dissolution
    (weaponized dissolved : IdentityState) : Prop :=
  weaponized_identity_under_shame weaponized ∧
  phase_coherent dissolved ∧
  weaponized.P = dissolved.P ∧
  weaponized.A < dissolved.A

-- Harm responsibility integration: the specific structural move of
-- acknowledging caused harm without sanitizing it, as a prerequisite
-- for sovereign redirect. Formalized as: the operator's narrative
-- axis (N) explicitly accumulates the acknowledgment of caused harm
-- rather than being reset to a pre-harm state. N grows to include
-- the harm history rather than being erased.
def harm_responsibility_integration
    (before after : IdentityState) : Prop :=
  before.N < after.N ∧
  after.pv > before.pv

-- Sovereign redirect at cost: sovereign choice deployed even when
-- the cost is extreme (self-sacrifice, extreme personal loss).
-- Formalized as: the operator's IVA dominance holds against a very
-- high F_ext class (representing the cost of the redirect), the
-- Pv strictly increases relative to the pre-redirect state, and
-- the state remains phase-coherent.
def sovereign_redirect_at_cost
    (before after : IdentityState) (cost : ℝ) : Prop :=
  cost > 0 ∧
  before.pv < after.pv ∧
  phase_coherent after ∧
  iva_dominance after cost

